name: 3.3.4-stable
body:

name: 3.2.3-stable
body:
**Godot 3.2.3** keeps making the 3.2 branch better suited for production use, with a wide range of bugfixes, both for recent regressions in 3.2.2 and older issues. There's also a new `.csproj` format for C# projects which should be better suited to the current .NET ecosystem.
Additionally, contributors improved usability, documentation and translations.

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/maintenance-release-godot-3-2-3)
- [Changelog](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/3.2.3/Godot_v3.2.3-stable_changelog_authors.txt)

name: 3.2.2-stable
body:
**Godot 3.2.2** improves upon the previous 3.2.1 release by adding a number of big features, such as C# support on iOS, 2D batching for the GLES2 renderer, a new plugin system for Android, and DTLS support in the networking stack.
Contributors also fixed numerous bugs, and improved usability, documentation and translations.

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/maintenance-release-godot-3-2-2)
- [Changelog](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/3.2.2/Godot_v3.2.2-stable_changelog_authors.txt)

name: 3.2-stable
body:
Godot contributors are thrilled and delighted to release our newest major update, **Godot 3.2**! It's the result of over 10 months of work by close to **450 contributors** (300 of them contributing to Godot for the first time) who authored more than 6000 commits!

Godot 3.2 is a major improvement over our previous 3.1 installment, bringing dozens of major features and hundreds of bugfixes and enhancements to bring our game developers an ever-improving feature set with a strong focus on usability.

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/here-comes-godot-3-2)
- [Changelog](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/3.2-stable/CHANGELOG.md)
- [Download](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/3.2)

name: 2.1.6-stable
body:
This maintenance update fixes some issues in the 2.1 branch, updates thirdparty libraries, and updates the export templates to matching changing distribution requirements of Google Play and Apple Store.
In particular, the Android templates now include x86_64 libraries and target the Android SDK 28. The iOS templates now target the iOS SDK 12.1.

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/maintenance-release-godot-2-1-6)
- [Changelog](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/2.1.6/Godot_v2.1.6-stable_changelog.txt)

name: 3.1.1-stable
body:
This maintenance update provides various important bug fixes in the new 3.1 stable branch in rendering, C# support and various other areas.

A forward incompatible change was made to the Object deserialization API to fix a security issue. GDNative plugins made for 3.1-stable should thus be recompiled for 3.1.1 and later.

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/maintenance-release-godot-3-1-1)
- [Changelog](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/3.1.1/Godot_v3.1.1-stable_changelog.txt)
- [Download](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/3.1.1/)

name: 3.1-stable
body:
After a bit more than one year of work, the Godot developers and contributors are delighted to get their new release out the door, Godot 3.1! It brings much-requested improvements to usability and many important features.

Noteworthy features are the OpenGL ES 2.0 renderer, optional typing in GDScript, lots of usability improvements in the editor UI, 2D skeletons and meshes, 3D soft bodies and ragdolls, and many other things.

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/godot-3-1-released)
- [Changelog](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/3.1-stable/CHANGELOG.md)
- [Download](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/3.1)

name: 2.1.5-stable
body:
This maintenance update brings many improvements over the previous 2.1.4-stable release, especially to distribute Godot games following Google Play and Apple Store's recent policy changes.

The release also fixes the same security vulnerability (CVE-2018-1000224) as [Godot 3.0.6](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/releases/tag/3.0.6-stable).

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/maintenance-release-godot-2-1-5)
- [Changelog](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/2.1.5/Godot_v2.1.5-stable_changelog.txt)
- [Download](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/2.1.5/)

name: 3.0.6-stable
body:
This maintenance update fixes a security vulnerability, and includes assorted bug fixes and enhancements.

Fabio Alessandrelli [found and fixed](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/issues/20558) several security vulnerabilities in the marshalling code of Godot Engine, which could be used by a remote Godot client to cause a Denial of Service for a Godot server (CVE-2018-1000224).

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/maintenance-release-godot-3-0-6)
- [Changelog](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/3.0.6-stable/CHANGELOG.md)

name: 3.0.5-stable
body:
This maintenance release fixes two main issues:
- Android export templates no longer contain the placeholder permissions which Google Play started complaining about. Now only requested permissions will be written to the manifest when exporting.
- User defined signals in the exported C# projects were misbehaving, this has now been fixed.

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/maintenance-release-godot-3-0-5)

This release brings the support for exporting C# based projects to Windows, Linux, and macOS! Over 350 patches were pulled into this release fixing various bugs and enhancement features - one notable change a new universal touch to mouse translation system.

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/maintenance-release-godot-3-0-3)

name: 3.0.2-stable
body:
This is a fairly small release but still something to be excited about! We found some small issues with the 3.0.1 release that we've decided were worth releasing a 3.0.2 for, the most important fix being that it's now again possible to run an individual scene of a project that does not have a main scene set. We also found the reason why tooltips were disappearing for some users, a bug that we've had for a long time.

We also have some love for C# users in this release: There was a regression using transforms from C#, and the commits that caused them have been reverted. Godot will now also no longer crash if you have a .mono directory created by an older release. This should make the C# workflow a lot better from now on.

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/maintenance-release-godot-302)
- [Changelog](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/3.0.2-stable/CHANGELOG.md)
- [Download](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/3.0.2/)

name: 3.0.1-stable
body:
We have added many new features to the editor (and several to GDScript) in this release which we think will make your use of Godot even better. We've also fixed several nagging issues and generally put together a really nice update for our users of the stable branch. 

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/maintenance-release-godot-3-0-1)
- [Changelog](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/8ea709a7a93dab01b0e33df168cba680ef016bf0/CHANGELOG.md)
- [Download](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/3.0.1/)

name: 3.0-stable
body:
After more than 18 months of development, all Godot Engine contributors are proud to present our biggest release so far, Godot 3.0! It brings a brand new rendering engine with state-of-the-art PBR workflow for 3D, an improved assets pipeline, GDNative to load native code as plugins, C# 7.0 support, Bullet as the 3D physics engine, and many other features!

- [Release notes](https://godotengine.org/article/godot-3-0-released)
- [Changelog](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/f2e19a26f556c42b7202072296dc072aaac2007c/CHANGELOG.md)
- [Download](https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/3.0/)
